description:
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We are looking for trained and experienced Phlebotomists to join our team.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Bay Medical Group is one of the largest GP Practices in the area and we provide general practice for over 52,000 patients. &lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We currently have an opportunity for a qualified Phlebotomist to join our friendly team in delivering excellent patient care and improving the health and well – being of the people of Morecambe.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The role is for 27 hours per week, working between the hours of 0730 and 1600 Monday – Friday.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;The successful candidate will be asked to work at any of our five sites in Morecambe and must be willing to work from any of these sites.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Your main duties will be to collect blood samples from patients and send them to the hospital laboratory for processing.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You will also need to be prepared to train to perform ECGs and carry out urinalysis.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;You must be patient- centred and committed to being part of a team providing excellent care and improving the lives of the people of Morecambe.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;BMG can offer you:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;A supportive team committed to the culture of staff wellbeing&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Regular team meetings&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Opportunity to develop skills&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Competitive Salary&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NHS pension scheme&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Annual leave that starts at 20 days and increases by a day each year to 25&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Access to occupational sick pay after one year&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;For informal discussion please contact Joshua Briody Clinical Nursing Operational Manager on 01524 511999.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;Interviews will be on 24&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt;th&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span&gt; November 2020.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Please note a DBS check will be required for the role if you are not a member of the DBS update service.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Successful applicants will be required to have sufficient English Language fluency as required under the Immigration Act 2016.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;We reserve the right to close the advert at any time if sufficient appropriate applications are received.&lt;br /&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;span&gt;&lt;strong&gt;We regret we can only contact candidates who are successful in reaching the interview stage of the recruitment process&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
